<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-08-0245 </DOCNO><TEXT>Recent figures make the future oil supply appear less problematic thanhitherto expected. For one thing, the proved reserves as of January 1,1988 are higher than expected. Secondly, there are considerable unprovedresources, and thirdly the nonconventional sources of oil are nearlyinexhaustible. On the other hand, these recent figures and statementstend to neglect the economic and political background and therefore maybe over-optimistic.</TEXT></DOC>